creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 147 by Various.
Read in English by Ian King; Son of the Exiles; Shakira Searle; Chris Pyle; Leonard Wilson; Bruce Kachuk; Newgatenovelist; Winston Tharp; Peter Tucker; John Perkins; Algy Pug; Claudia Salto
This is a collection of 27 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for August 2015. It includes:
After the Last Breath, by Thomas Hardy The Armada, by Thomas Babington Macaulay Ashes of Life, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Beauty, by Charles Baudelaire Book Lover, by Robert W. Service A Career, by Paul Laurence Dunbar A Child’s Laughter, by Algernon Charles Swinburne The Dancers, by Michael Field Down by the Salley Gardens, by William Butler Yeats Sonnet XXXVII (Fair is my love that feeds among the lilies), by Bartholomew Griffin A Farewell to Arms, by George Peele First Love, by John Clare Forgiveness, by George William Russell A Lazy Day, by Paul Laurence Dunbar Life Is Struggle, by Arthur Hugh Clough Morning, by Paul Laurence Dunbar Oak and Olive, by James Elroy Flecker On the Death of Sir Philip Sidney, by Henry Constable She Walks in Beauty, by George Gordon, Lord Byron Song of Khan Zada, by Laurence Hope A Song of Republics, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox Sorrow, by Edna St. Vincent Millay Stanzas for Music, by George Gordon, Lord Byron The True Knight, by Stephen Hawes Wail of an Old-timer, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox Sonnet VII (When I too long have looked upon your face), by Edna St. Vincent Millay When Mother Reads Aloud, by Unknown For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
